you can sort a List using `Collections.sort`.

given your `Fund`:

    List&lt;Fund&gt; sortMe = new ArrayList(...);
    Collections.sort(sortMe, new Comparator&lt;Fund&gt;() {
      @Override
      public int compare(Fund left, Fund right) {
